HEADWORD: Lyencephala
<hw>Ly`en*ceph"a*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ to loose + <?/ the brain.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
group of Mammalia, including the marsupials and monotremes; -- so called
because the corpus callosum is rudimentary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lyencephalous</ent>⟦br⟧
